<span id="freeTextContainer11183642546860354561">This book bordered on a religious revelation to me. I absolutely adore the style it is written in and the subject matter tears at the fabric of your understanding of reality. I questioned what I know in a way that harkens back to Plato&apos;s &apos;The Cave&apos;. Is reality real or is it just shadows on the wall inside something bigger than I can understand?<br/><br/>Clive Barker has a way of making dark and sinister characters intriguing and not nightmare inducing. </span>
  <span id="freeText11183642546860354561" style="display:none">This book bordered on a religious revelation to me. I absolutely adore the style it is written in and the subject matter tears at the fabric of your understanding of reality. I questioned what I know in a way that harkens back to Plato's 'The Cave'. Is reality real or is it just shadows on the wall inside something bigger than I can understand?<br /><br />Clive Barker has a way of making dark and sinister characters intriguing and not nightmare inducing. </span>
